									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Product &#8211; I had been thinking spaceship of some sort &#8211; your idea for universe starter is great and I wish I had thought of it. Perhaps I will include it in a rewrite. I think a bit more length and some language tightening might make me really like this one so a rewrite is likely.</p>
<p>Don&#8217;t understand wrt comma after future, perhaps my meaning is really unclear. The sentence might read better if I made like thrust testing was a proper noun and got a earlier comma:  ‚ÄúDue to the cost in equipment and danger to key personnel, all future Thrust Testing &#8230;&#8221;</p>
<p>Rest of your nits are clear and useful, &#8216;timidly&#8217; in that spot looks terrible to me now; I wonder if anyone else had difficulty with &#8216;So I never told them&#8217;?</p>
