				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>I loved this and found it very, very funny. It was great to read something that is so typical of what one experiences and has heard about in our mundane world, yet transferred completely to a fantasy genre. </p>
<p>I think you captured the business and technical speak beautifully, and I love the humour added by the descriptions of aliens. Especially, the &#8220;Subspace Team‚Äôs stuttering giggle-squeaks&#8221;, which had me giggling a lot.</p>
<p>I quite liked not knowing what the product was &#8211; it made the story more general and seemed somehow unimportant (like it doesn&#8217;t matter what you are making, these silly political and bureaucratic plays will happen). </p>
<p>I would like the Steering Committee to be capitalised consistently.</p>
<p>Thanks. This was a lot of fun.</p>
