				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>I loved the bureaucracy in this, and the satire around the recasting of things to fit the political climate. Made me laugh <img src="http://localhost:8888/microfiction.co.za/wp-includes/images/smilies/simple-smile.png" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> I think it was quite well done.</p>
<p>I didn&#8217;t have a problem with, &#8220;So I never told them&#8230;&#8221; I assumed that it was related to the removal of engineering types from the Steering Committee. Since there was no longer anyone in the committee to tell, he never told them. </p>
<p>I also feel that there should be a comma after &#8220;personnel&#8221;, and possibly also:<br />
&gt; Timidly[,] the new intern<br />
and possibly also (but it doesn&#8217;t stand out to much in this one)<br />
&gt; Unfortunately[,] all engineering</p>
<p>Also, while people have been complaining about inconsistent capitalisation (I never noticed the one about the steering committee, though), &#8220;Sir&#8221; is used in the same person&#8217;s dialogue both capitalised and uncapitalised.</p>
<p>This was fun. Thanks üòâ</p>
